		{"id":"637b0d1ed1357459","x":-480,"y":1340,"width":340,"height":60,"color":"6","type":"text","text":"# 3 - Progettazione"},
		{"id":"6fcc70c5f7b02cad","x":-860,"y":1488,"width":589,"height":512,"type":"text","text":"# Schema modello-design\nidentifica per ogni canale\n- i borders dell'applicazione, di ogni tipo (tecnici quanto morali/legali)\n- i possibili stati (e.g. triviale finite state automata): i punti ciechi (try-catch in java)\n- i possibili stimoli esterni, e di conseguenza\n- le possibili risposte agli stimoli esterni\n- in anticipo, possibilmente, le future evoluzioni\n\nmodel is asking questions, design is answer. to achive good design a good question is \"what can break my application?\".\n\nspesso il software parte da un obiettivo o una richiesta"},
		{"id":"b9339531870691e7","type":"text","text":"## touch screen\n\nearly ones were gigantic cause of poor resolution.can detect the presence and location of a touch within the display area\n• Resistive: Resistive touch is used in restaurants, factories and hospitals due to\nits high resistance to liquids and contaminants\n• Capacitive: As the human body is also an electrical conductor, touching the\nsurface of the screen results in a distortion of the screen's electrostatic field,\nmeasurable as a change in capacitance.\n• Infrared: beams of infrared rays are interrupted by user finger","x":-1600,"y":-39,"width":445,"height":429,"color":"1"},
